JSE-listed Murray & Roberts (M&R) has adjourned a general meeting that had initially been set to be held on February 13. The meeting will be reconvened on February 20 at 11:00 on the 9th Floor at the Interchange Building, 22 Skeen Boulevard, Bedfordview, Johannesburg, the minimum period as prescribed by the Companies Act. This is to allow the board of directors and management to conclude discussions with key stakeholders regarding the disposal by M&R of its entire direct and indirect shareholding in Bombela Concession Company. Forms of proxy submitted for the initial general meeting will remain valid in respect of the adjournment of the general meeting. No further action will be required by shareholders who have submitted forms of proxy.